title: Phish - PMCLP 1993 Part 6 (Pretty Much Complete Live Phish)
description:
Phish - PMCLP 1993 Part 6 (Pretty Much Complete Live Phish)


This is a repost of a Demonoid torrent, "Pretty Much Complete Live Phish" 

(PMCLP).  Basically, it is a catalog of "pretty much" every Phish show in 

circulation from before 10/07/2000 (Phish ended their first hiatus on 

12/31/2002, and henceforth all recordings have been available via LivePhish).  

Some are SBD, but by far mostly AUD; all have recording info; all are tagged, 

and even have artwork which corresponds to the ticket stub or venue; NONE of 

this is in FLAC:  This is exactly how this torrent was seeded about 5 years 

ago.  Some are 320, but most are lower bitrates.  However, the point is that 

many - if not most - of these recordings are not available at 

bt.etree.org...but if they are, I heartily suggest you head over there and 

download that and any other shows you like in wonderful FLAC.  If I find that 

any of these shows are available via bt.etree.org in FLAC I will upload that 

as well.  I am offering this collection up because it is comprehensive:  it 

really does comprise almost every Phish show in circulation from before the 

first hiatus.  I am really anal about FLAC/320 just like most of you, but the 

vast majority of these shows offered here are not presently available in the 

bittorrent community in any other format (although, once again, some are 

available at bt.etree.org, and some though Phish.com).

This is the sixth of roughly 50 torrents which comprise the whole collection, 

which goes from 1984 - 2000, and the last for 1993.  August 1993 is one of 

those top-shelf, month-long, superlative moments in Phish history, along with 

Fall 1997 and April 1992, for example.
